TOOL_USE: Write({"file_path": "/home/joe/Documents/repo/skill/sci-draw/.claude/_eval_sandbox_home/.claude/plans/tranquil-booping-ripple.md", "content": "# Interactive Sensor Dashboard Plan\n\n## Context\n\nThe user wants an interactive dashboard to display real-time laboratory sensor data, with filtering by time range and device type. Data comes from a PostgreSQL database. This is a greenfield project built alongside the existing `sci-draw` skill in the same repo.\n\n## Design Decisions\n\n- **Framework**: Dash (Plotly's dashboard framework) — provides built-in interactive components (date pickers, dropdowns, graph callbacks), significantly less glue code than Flask+Plotly.\n- **DB driver**: `psycopg2-binary` for PostgreSQL connectivity.\n- **Schema**: A general-purpose sensor readings schema (see below), with a seed script to populate mock data for development/testing.\n- **Project layout**: All dashboard files under a new `dashboard/` directory at repo root.\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\ndashboard/\n├── app.py                  # Dash app entry point, layout, callbacks\n├── db.py                   # PostgreSQL connection + query functions\n├── schema.sql              # DDL for sensor tables\n├── seed_data.py            # Script to insert mock sensor data\n├── requirements.txt        # Dash-specific dependencies\n└── assets/\n    └── custom.css          # Dashboard styling\n```\n\n### Database Schema\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE devices (\n    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n    device_type VARCHAR(64) NOT NULL,\n    device_name VARCHAR(128) NOT NULL,\n    location VARCHAR(128),\n    installed_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE sensor_readings (\n    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n    device_id INT REFERENCES devices(id),\n    timestamp TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),\n    temperature DOUBLE PRECISION,\n    humidity DOUBLE PRECISION,\n    pressure DOUBLE PRECISION,\n    extra JSONB\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_readings_device_time ON sensor_readings(device_id, timestamp DESC);\nCREATE INDEX idx_readings_time ON sensor_readings(timestamp DESC);\n```\n\n### Dashboard Layout\n\n- **Top bar**: Title + auto-refresh toggle (every N seconds)\n- **Left sidebar filters**:\n  - Device type dropdown (multi-select)\n  - Date/time range picker (start → end)\n  - \"Apply Filters\" button\n- **Main panel (tabbed or grid)**:\n  - Time-series line chart (temperature/humidity/pressure over time, colored by device)\n  - Latest readings table (most recent N rows)\n  - Summary stats cards (avg, min, max per metric)\n\n### Key Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `dashboard/schema.sql` | Table DDL + indexes |\n| `dashboard/db.py` | Connection pool, `query_readings(device_types, start, end)` function |\n| `dashboard/app.py` | Dash app with layout, callbacks for filtering + auto-refresh |\n| `dashboard/seed_data.py` | Insert 3 device types × 2 devices × 1000 readings each = 6000 mock rows |\n| `dashboard/requirements.txt` | `dash`, `psycopg2-binary`, `pandas`, `plotly` |\n\n### Callback Flow\n\n1. User selects device types → `dcc.Dropdown` value changes\n2. User picks date range → `dcc.DatePickerRange` value changes\n3. Auto-refresh `dcc.Interval` fires every 30s\n4. Any of the above triggers the main callback → `db.query_readings(...)` → returns DataFrame\n5. DataFrame updates 3 outputs simultaneously:\n   - `dcc.Graph` (time-series line chart)\n   - `dash_table.DataTable` (latest readings)\n   - `html.Div` children (summary stat cards)\n\n### Dependencies to Install\n\nInstall into `sensor_venv`:\n```\npip install dash psycopg2-binary pandas plotly\n```\n\nPandas and Plotly are already in the system pip but not in the venv.\n\n## Implementation Steps\n\n1. **Create `dashboard/` directory and `requirements.txt`**\n2. **Write `schema.sql`** — DDL with devices + sensor_readings tables\n3. **Write `db.py`** — connection pool, parameterized read query\n4. **Write `seed_data.py`** — mock data generator\n5. **Write `app.py`** — full Dash application (layout + callbacks)\n6. **Write `assets/custom.css`** — basic styling\n7. **Install dependencies and test** — run `python app.py`, open browser\n\n## Verification\n\n1. Run `python dashboard/seed_data.py` to populate the DB with mock data\n2. Run `python dashboard/app.py` — server starts on `http://127.0.0.1:8050`\n3. Verify: time-series chart renders, device type filter works, date range filter narrows data, auto-refresh updates without page reload, summary stats match visible data\n"})
